lines.text: i feel so bad, got a worried mind;
i'm so lonesome all of the time
since i left my baby behind
working till the sun don't shine
come what may to blue bayou
and-the world is mine on blue bayou
with-their sails afloat,if i could only see
through sleepy eyes, how happy i'd be
gonna be with some of my friends
working till the sun don't shine
looking forward to happier times on blue bayou
come what may to blue bayou
and-the world is mine on blue bayou
with-their sails afloat, if i could only see
through sleepy eyes, how happy i'd be
oh that boy of mine by my side,
the silver moon and the evening time
gonna take away this hurtin' inside

paragraphs.text: i feel so bad, got a worried mind; i'm so lonesome all of the time since i left my baby behind on blue bayou
saving nickels, saving dimes; working till the sun don't shine looking forward to happier times on blue bayou

i'm going back some day, come what may to blue bayou where the folks are fine, and-the world is mine on blue bayou where those fishing boats with-their sails afloat,if i could only see that familiar sunrise through sleepy eyes, how happy i'd be
gonna see my baby again gonna be with some of my friends maybe i'll feel better again on blue bayou
saving nickels, saving dimes working till the sun don't shine looking forward to happier times on blue bayou

i'm going back someday, come what may to blue bayou where the folks are fine, and-the world is mine on blue bayou where those fishing boats with-their sails afloat, if i could only see that familiar sunrise through sleepy eyes, how happy i'd be
oh that boy of mine by my side, the silver moon and the evening time oh, some sweet day, gonna take away this hurtin' inside well i'd never be blue, my dreams come true on blue bayou
